# Module Pages

- Required page: `docs/README.md` (and `docs/README.ru.md` for RU).
- README content creation rules:
  - first paragraphs should describe module purpose without a heading;
  - in the first 1-2 sentences explicitly state module audience and scope (who it is for and what task it solves), without implementation details;
  - keep introductory part within 2-3 short paragraphs to avoid a mini-manual;
  - `## Main Features` (RU: `## –û—Å–Ω–æ–≤–Ω—ã–µ –≤–æ–∑–º–æ–∂–Ω–æ—Å—Ç–∏`) should be present as second-level heading;
  - `Main Features` should contain up to 7 bullet points;
  - each feature bullet must describe user value ("what it gives the user"), avoid generic wording and marketing language;
  - do not add information about how to enable or disable the module.
  - keep README overview-oriented; move detailed setup/operations instructions to dedicated pages (`USAGE`, `USER_GUIDE`, `ADMIN_GUIDE`, etc.).
  - if usage limitations exist, add a dedicated second-level section (`## Limitations` / `## –û–≥—Ä–∞–Ω–∏—á–µ–Ω–∏—è`) with explicit non-covered cases.
- `CR` pages are required only if YAML files exist directly in `crds/` root (no subfolders).
- `CONFIGURATION` pages are required only if `openapi/config-values.yaml` exists in `openapi/` root (no subfolders).

# Optional Pages

- Optional: `USAGE`, `EXAMPLES`, `FAQ`, `ADVANCED_USAGE`, `ARCHITECTURE`.
- Optional: `USER_GUIDE`, `ADMIN_GUIDE`.
- Create optional pages only when they add real reader value for module scenarios.

# Notes

- If a conditional page is not applicable, do not create an empty placeholder page.
